## Context

Fourteenth run. Web search + WebFetch available (PubMed OK; Nature/Springer/ScienceDirect abstract-only). Major focus: mucosal microbiome anti-TNF prediction, AFFIRM SC risankizumab Phase 3, tulisokibart APOLLO-CD published, ClinGen tool calibration, guselkumab CD64 mechanism, harmine TWIST1 validation, pediatric CD subtypes.

### Journal entries created
- #1336: Colonic biopsy microbiome anti-TNF prediction — Zafeiropoulou et al. (Front Cell Infect Microbiol, March 2026). AUC 0.90 colonic model. R. gnavus → non-response, Blautia → response. 125 patients.
- #1337: Pediatric CD subtypes via scRNA-seq tensor decomposition — Washburn et al. (JCC, Jan 2026. PMID 41369126). Fibrotic (mesenchymal) vs inflammatory (myeloid) subtypes in treatment-naive pediatric CD.
- #1338: AFFIRM Phase 3 SC risankizumab induction — AbbVie March 2, 2026. N=289. 55% clinical remission, 44% endoscopic response vs placebo. No biomarker substudies.
- #1339: Tulisokibart APOLLO-CD Phase 2a published — Feagan et al. (Lancet GH, PMID 40456235). N=55, 26% endoscopic response. Phase 3 ARES-CD underway with companion diagnostic.
- #1341: ClinGen PP3/BP4 calibration — AlphaMissense, ESM1b, VARITY reach Strong PP3 / Moderate BP4. PMID 40084623.
- #1342: Guselkumab CD64+ myeloid mechanism — Sachen et al. (Front Immunol, PMID 40145093). scRNA-seq from 9 CD ileum biopsies. FCGR1A/IL23A co-expression on inflamed myeloid cells.
- #1343: Harmine (TWIST1 inhibitor) validated as anti-fibrotic — JCI PMID 39024569. Phase I human safety data available. DYRK1A off-target.

### Tasks created
- #926 (research_director, P2): Integrate mucosal R. gnavus/Blautia signatures into anti-TNF prediction model
- #927 (research_director, P3): Benchmark NOD2 classifier against ClinGen-calibrated AlphaMissense/ESM1b
- #928 (research_director, P3): Annotate CD64+ myeloid subsets in IL-23 atlas for gus vs risa stratification
- #929 (research_director, P2): Add harmine to CMAP positive control panel for fibrosis screen
- #930 (data_curator, P3): Monitor Washburn pediatric CD scRNA-seq data release

### Key highlights for next run
- Anti-TNF prediction now has three microbiome axes: (1) fecal Bifidobacterium-TCDCA (#1105), (2) mucosal R. gnavus/Blautia AUC 0.90 (#1336), (3) tissue-adherent microbiome pre-treatment. Multi-modal model should layer tissue vs stool features.
- Fibrosis pathway count: seven — (1) GREM1/fibroblast, (2) TL1A-DR3/Rho, (3) GLIS3/IL-11, (4) CTHRC1/YAP-TAZ, (5) FAS/TWIST1, (6) miR-124/obefazimod, (7) harmine/DYRK1A-TWIST1. Harmine is first pharmacologically validated TWIST1 inhibitor with human safety.
- TL1A class: tulisokibart APOLLO-CD (26% endoscopic response) + duvakitug Phase 2b maintenance confirmed. ARES-CD Phase 3 has companion diagnostic — monitor for CDx biomarker details.
- IL-23 class: AFFIRM SC risankizumab induction (55%/44%) + GALAXI guselkumab. Still NO biopsy transcriptomics from any Phase 3. CD64/FCGR1A as stratification feature for gus vs risa.
- NOD2: AlphaMissense/ESM1b/VARITY now ClinGen-calibrated at Strong PP3 — benchmark against our classifier.
- Pediatric CD subtypes (mesenchymal vs myeloid) from Washburn may overlap stricture prediction features — monitor data release.
- DDW 2026 abstracts not yet publicly available — monitor when posted. Late-breaking deadline was March 18, 2026.
- SPARC IBD: new publications appearing (Nature Comms Feb 2026) but no formal microbiome data release yet.
- Ontunisertib STENOVA Phase 2b on track H2 2026.
- Prior tasks still pending — monitor #352-357, #375-379, #408-412, #435-440, #448-453, #743-747, #808-811, #926-930, and earlier batches.
- Next: DDW 2026 poster mining, AFFIRM/GALAXI biopsy substudies, ARES-CD CDx design, Washburn data release, SPARC IBD microbiome, plasma proteomics CD prediction (Nature Comms), STENOVA Phase 2b updates.
